on": "clear", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.6726242303848267, "span": {"begin": 487, "end": 492}}, {"id": ["mesh:D003537"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "clear cell cystadenoma", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9979903101921082, "span": {"begin": 487, "end": 509}}, {"id": ["mesh:D049291"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "seromucinous systadenoma", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999992847442627, "span": {"begin": 514, "end": 538}}, {"id": ["mesh:D018293"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "ovarian serous cystadenoma", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999825954437256, "span": {"begin": 564, "end": 590}}, {"id": ["mesh:D018284"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "serous carcinoma", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999986290931702, "span": {"begin": 612, "end": 628}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:673"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "BRAF", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9936566948890686, "span": {"begin": 683, "end": 687}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3845"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "KRAS", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9748299717903137, "span": {"begin": 692, "end": 696}}, {"id": ["mesh:D018284"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "serous carcinoma", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.999998152256012, "span": {"begin": 733, "end": 749}}], "text": "Ovarian tumors are abnormal mass of tissues grows on or in the ovaries of the aged females. Ovarian adenomas / cystadenomas are very common and benign type of tumors, which are found in epithelial tissues of the ovaries. Almost 60% of the ovarian tumors are due to the epithelial neoplasm (abnormal growth of tissue) of the ovary (Limaiem et al. 2022). Ovarian adenomas are classified into different categories such as serous cystadenoma, mucinous cystadenoma, endometrioid cystadenoma, clear cell cystadenoma and seromucinous systadenoma. Reports have shown that ovarian serous cystadenoma can turn progress to serous carcinoma (Cheng et al. 2004). Frequent mutations of two genes (BRAF and KRAS) are identified as the cause of the serous carcinoma.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:41:45 +0000 2026"}